<emphasis box="[292,492,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Convoluta 
<taxonomicName box="[411,492,1626,1649]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="niphoni" status="sp. nov.">niphoni</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[501,588,1625,1649]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[501,588,1625,1649]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; reconstructions to show arrangement of organs. A. Sagittal reconstruction of whole specimen. B. Dorsal view. The gonads are paired, but for clarity, just the left testes and right ovaries are shown. C. Female and male copulatory organs.
</paragraph>
